modules.name: AWS.CodeStar
modules.comments:
AWS CodeStar

This is the API reference for AWS CodeStar. This reference provides descriptions of the operations and data types for the AWS CodeStar API along with usage examples.

You can use the AWS CodeStar API to work with:

Projects and their resources, by calling the following:

  • DeleteProject, which deletes a project.

  • DescribeProject, which lists the attributes of a project.

  • ListProjects, which lists all projects associated with your AWS account.

  • ListResources, which lists the resources associated with a project.

  • ListTagsForProject, which lists the tags associated with a project.

  • TagProject, which adds tags to a project.

  • UntagProject, which removes tags from a project.

  • UpdateProject, which updates the attributes of a project.

Teams and team members, by calling the following:

  • AssociateTeamMember, which adds an IAM user to the team for a project.

  • DisassociateTeamMember, which removes an IAM user from the team for a project.

  • ListTeamMembers, which lists all the IAM users in the team for a project, including their roles and attributes.

  • UpdateTeamMember, which updates a team member's attributes in a project.

Users, by calling the following:

  • CreateUserProfile, which creates a user profile that contains data associated with the user across all projects.

  • DeleteUserProfile, which deletes all user profile information across all projects.

  • DescribeUserProfile, which describes the profile of a user.

  • ListUserProfiles, which lists all user profiles.

  • UpdateUserProfile, which updates the profile for a user.

declarations.comments: Adds an IAM user to the team for an AWS CodeStar project.
declarations.title: associateTeamMember

declarations.comments: Reserved for future use. To create a project, use the AWS CodeStar console.
declarations.title: createProject

declarations.comments: Creates a profile for a user that includes user preferences, such as the display name and email address assocciated with the user, in AWS CodeStar. The user profile is not project-specific. Information in the user profile is displayed wherever the user's information appears to other users in AWS CodeStar.
declarations.title: createUserProfile

declarations.comments: Deletes a project, including project resources. Does not delete users associated with the project, but does delete the IAM roles that allowed access to the project.
declarations.title: deleteProject

declarations.comments: Deletes a user profile in AWS CodeStar, including all personal preference data associated with that profile, such as display name and email address. It does not delete the history of that user, for example the history of commits made by that user.
declarations.title: deleteUserProfile

declarations.comments: Describes a project and its resources.
declarations.title: describeProject

declarations.comments: Describes a user in AWS CodeStar and the user attributes across all projects.
declarations.title: describeUserProfile

declarations.comments: Removes a user from a project. Removing a user from a project also removes the IAM policies from that user that allowed access to the project and its resources. Disassociating a team member does not remove that user's profile from AWS CodeStar. It does not remove the user from IAM.
declarations.title: disassociateTeamMember

declarations.comments: Lists all projects in AWS CodeStar associated with your AWS account.
declarations.title: listProjects

declarations.comments: Lists resources associated with a project in AWS CodeStar.
declarations.title: listResources

declarations.comments: Gets the tags for a project.
declarations.title: listTagsForProject

declarations.comments: Lists all team members associated with a project.
declarations.title: listTeamMembers

declarations.comments: Lists all the user profiles configured for your AWS account in AWS CodeStar.
declarations.title: listUserProfiles

declarations.comments: Adds tags to a project.
declarations.title: tagProject

declarations.comments: Removes tags from a project.
declarations.title: untagProject

declarations.comments: Updates a project in AWS CodeStar.
declarations.title: updateProject

declarations.comments: Updates a team member's attributes in an AWS CodeStar project. For example, you can change a team member's role in the project, or change whether they have remote access to project resources.
declarations.title: updateTeamMember

declarations.comments: Updates a user's profile in AWS CodeStar. The user profile is not project-specific. Information in the user profile is displayed wherever the user's information appears to other users in AWS CodeStar.
declarations.title: updateUserProfile

declarations.comments: Another modification is being made. That modification must complete before you can make your change.
declarations.title: ConcurrentModificationException

declarations.comments: The next token is not valid.
declarations.title: InvalidNextTokenException

declarations.comments: The service role is not valid.
declarations.title: InvalidServiceRoleException

declarations.comments: A resource limit has been exceeded.
declarations.title: LimitExceededException

declarations.comments: An AWS CodeStar project with the same ID already exists in this region for the AWS account. AWS CodeStar project IDs must be unique within a region for the AWS account.
declarations.title: ProjectAlreadyExistsException

declarations.comments: Project configuration information is required but not specified.
declarations.title: ProjectConfigurationException

declarations.comments: The project creation request was valid, but a nonspecific exception or error occurred during project creation. The project could not be created in AWS CodeStar.
declarations.title: ProjectCreationFailedException

declarations.comments: The specified AWS CodeStar project was not found.
declarations.title: ProjectNotFoundException

declarations.comments: Information about the metadata for a project.
declarations.title: ProjectSummary

declarations.comments: Information about a resource for a project.
declarations.title: Resource

declarations.comments: Information about a team member in a project.
declarations.title: TeamMember

declarations.comments: The team member is already associated with a role in this project.
declarations.title: TeamMemberAlreadyAssociatedException

declarations.comments: The specified team member was not found.
declarations.title: TeamMemberNotFoundException

declarations.comments: A user profile with that name already exists in this region for the AWS account. AWS CodeStar user profile names must be unique within a region for the AWS account.
declarations.title: UserProfileAlreadyExistsException

declarations.comments: The user profile was not found.
declarations.title: UserProfileNotFoundException

declarations.comments: Information about a user's profile in AWS CodeStar.
declarations.title: UserProfileSummary

declarations.comments: The specified input is either not valid, or it could not be validated.
declarations.title: ValidationException
